CatDescriptText: The lead headline in city edition of the Pittsburgh Courier in the window reads"Nat'l Drive to Halt Construction" and subheading, "Pittsburgh Prime Target". Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 11, 1970, pg. 24, reads: "Model Cities Elections - the following areas have nominated these Candidates for Chairmanship and Vice-Chairmanship of their respective neighborhood planning teams...Muhammed Aziz, Ruby Huddleston, Margaret Robinson, Winifred Smith. Not shown, but in the running - Rebecca Johnson, James Johnson...Area V, Monday, July 13, 1970, 7:30 P.M., Place: Ozanam Center, 1833 Wylie Avenue, Pittsburgh, Pa. 15219"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Muhammed Aziz, Ruby "Daisy" Huddleston, Margaret Robinson, and Winifred Smith, standing in front of New Pittsburgh Courier offices, Carson Street, South Side
